snippet.textDisplay:
Whoa.. The original musical is great in my opinion. The story is straightforward: each year the group of cats known as the Jellicles has a sort of voting on who will be reborn into a new life in the Heaviside layer. The elder cat, Deuterotomy, is depressed during the Jellicle ball because he doesn't understand what happiness is, he doesn't understand why there is a celebration and what he is even deciding. Grizabella the Glamour Cat - now washed up and cast out of the tribe - recalls a memory of what happiness was and wishes to be accepted again. For that, Deuterotomy gifts her the honor to go to the Heaviside layer.

I mean, it is the most successful musical. People loved it when it was out. The music is great, the costume design is amazing, and the set design is fantastic. These things are what you can't ignore - but then again this isn't a review for the musical.

snippet.textDisplay:
Blaming furries for the way the Cats movie looks is like blaming furries for the way Old Movie Sonic looked.
If furries were in charge it would end up falling somewhere in a triangle plot between the Sonic OVA, Disney's Robin Hood and a Chuck Jones cartoon without the over-the-top off-model adventures.


That said, I'm pretty sure the designs in both the Cats movie and Old Movie Sonic are pandering to someone's sexual proclivities. That person is deranged and unsettling even by the typical Furry's standards, and if they're in a Producer position in Hollywood then we should all be very, very afraid.

snippet.textDisplay: The plot of Cats summarized: A bunch of London's stray cats get together once a year to dance and caterwaul, with some competing for the opportunity to be euthanized, alluded to euphemistically as ascending to the "Heaviside Layer." An aged old feline named "Old Deuteronomy" chooses the winner. Grizabella, an especially squalid cat who can't stop moaning about her lost beauty, is chosen as the winner after wailing an especially lugubrious semi-dirge. She ascends to her eternal reward on an apparently magical chandelier.
